The paper deals with improving the performance of LTE networks through the use of dynamic frequency reuse techniques, which is a topic that falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed solution involves the use of neural networks to make decisions, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of multiple agents to coordinate the network also suggests a focus on distributed systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with optimizing network performance, which is a topic that falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
